00:44:12.120 --> 00:44:15.420
that, in this case,
is Hofman, et al.,

00:44:15.420 --> 00:44:18.700
and the title is "Relearning
Sound Localization

00:44:18.700 --> 00:44:20.490
with New Ears."

00:44:20.490 --> 00:44:23.770
And so, in a nutshell, what
they did in that research report

00:44:23.770 --> 00:44:26.510
was they took little
pieces of clay,

00:44:26.510 --> 00:44:31.050
and they inserted them into
their external ears or pinna,

00:44:31.050 --> 00:44:35.070
and therefore distorted
quite a lot your pinnae.

00:44:35.070 --> 00:44:36.550
They couldn't do
what van Gogh did,

00:44:36.550 --> 00:44:39.270
which was cut off the
pinna, but they certainly

00:44:39.270 --> 00:44:42.140
distorted their pinnaes
quite a lot on both sides.

00:44:43.190 --> 00:44:45.430
And then they tested,
using themselves

00:44:45.430 --> 00:44:47.690
as subjects and
other volunteers,

00:44:47.690 --> 00:44:51.115
how good their ability
to localize sound was.

00:44:52.210 --> 00:44:56.310
And especially in terms of when
the sound varied in elevation,

00:44:56.310 --> 00:44:58.500
they found that there
were huge differences,

00:44:58.500 --> 00:45:02.140
that they couldn't localize
sounds that were straight ahead

00:45:02.140 --> 00:45:05.585
versus sounds that were
coming from above themselves

00:45:05.585 --> 00:45:06.543
with these distortions.

00:45:07.950 --> 00:45:10.470
But what was funny
and what harks back

00:45:10.470 --> 00:45:13.310
to the title of the
article is that when

00:45:13.310 --> 00:45:17.550
they had the volunteers go out
and live their normal lives

00:45:17.550 --> 00:45:21.600
with these pinna distortions
in for a few weeks,

00:45:21.600 --> 00:45:25.520
then they came back into the
lab and tested them again,

00:45:25.520 --> 00:45:30.760
they found that they could now
localize sounds in elevation

00:45:30.760 --> 00:45:32.560
with these new ears.

00:45:32.560 --> 00:45:34.790
They relearned how
to localize sound.

00:45:34.790 --> 00:45:38.570
So this is a nice demonstration
of learning or plasticity,

00:45:38.570 --> 00:45:40.560
at least in
psychophysical responses.

00:45:42.280 --> 00:45:44.370
And it also emphasizes
the function

00:45:44.370 --> 00:45:47.750
of your external ear, which
helps you localize sounds

00:45:47.750 --> 00:45:48.250
in space.

